# History: batch-low-difficulty-issue-impl

## v1.7.0 (2026-04-24)

**Changed by:** Myrmidons shellcheck-warnings myrmidon swarm session (2026-04-24)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added Myrmidons 2026-04-24 session summary row (shellcheck-warnings swarm)
- Added Phase 0.5: Pre-Swarm Existing-PR Audit section with close-before-delegate pattern
- Added hot-file serialization note to Phase 3 (Group by Target File)
- Added 2 new "When to Use" conditions: hot-file serialization (#8) and pre-swarm PR audit (#9)
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts entries:
  - Launching without checking existing PRs: 8 existing PRs discovered after dispatch
  - Two agents touching apply.sh in same sub-wave: merge conflict guaranteed
  - Delegating to agent when issue already had a PR: duplicate agent noise
- Added Myrmidons session statistics table
- Added HomericIntelligence/Myrmidons to Verified On table
- Updated description to mention hot-file serialization and pre-swarm PR audit
- Bumped version 1.6.0 → 1.7.0, updated date to 2026-04-24

### Why
Myrmidons shellcheck-warnings swarm (2026-04-24) revealed two new failure modes:
1. Launching without checking existing PRs: 8 open PRs already existed; agents duplicated work. Fix: always audit `gh pr list --state open` before any dispatch.
2. Hot-file conflicts: `scripts/apply.sh` and `scripts/lib/reconcile.sh` are touched by many issues. Two agents in the same sub-wave caused a merge conflict. Fix: hot-file serialization — at most 1 agent per hot file per sub-wave.

