## v1.2.0 (2026-04-23)

**Changed by:** ProjectArgus issue triage session (23 issues triaged, 3 PRs merged)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added new Failed Attempts entry: worktree agents inheriting wrong git base from L0 non-main branch
- Extended Verified Workflow Phase 3 with mandatory branch-base check before dispatching agents

### Why
During ProjectArgus batch triage, 3 Haiku agents were dispatched with `isolation: "worktree"` while L0 was on branch `15-exporter-port-9101`. Worktrees inherited that as base, adding 4-5 unrelated commits to each PR branch. GitHub refused rebase merge ("This branch can't be rebased"). Fix required cherry-pick + force-push per branch. Prevention: explicit `git checkout -B <branch> origin/main` in agent prompts.

---

